# Performance Results Directory

This directory stores performance test results and baselines.

## Files

- `latest.txt` - Symlink to the most recent performance report
- `latest.json` - Symlink to the most recent JSON results
- `perf_<version>_<timestamp>.txt` - Human-readable performance reports
- `perf_<version>_<timestamp>.json` - Machine-readable JSON results
- `baselines/` - Performance baselines for each release

## Running Performance Tests

```bash
# Run all performance tests and save results
./scripts/run_perf_tests.sh --save

# Compare with a baseline
./scripts/run_perf_tests.sh --compare perf-results/baselines/v0.1.0/latest.json
```

## Performance Targets

| Metric                          | Target      |
|---------------------------------|-------------|
| Strategy selection              | < 10 us     |
| Pool creation (20 endpoints)    | < 1 ms      |
| Stats update                    | < 1 us      |
| Metrics collection              | < 100 us    |
| Concurrent throughput           | > 100k/sec  |
